# React Component Structure

## Design System Check (MANDATORY before any new component)

Before building a new component, check whether a Radix UI or `components/ui/` equivalent already exists:

1. Check `components/ui/` for an existing shadcn/Radix component.
2. If a match exists → import and use it. Do **not** recreate it locally.
3. If no match exists → build a local component in the appropriate domain folder.
4. **If in doubt** whether a shared component exists for the use case — **ask before building**.

## Component Structure

- Functional components only — no class components.
- Named exports only — no default exports except page files (`app/**/page.tsx`).
- Props interface must extend the relevant HTML element attributes and `Omit` conflicting props.
- Use `React.forwardRef` + set `displayName` for any component reused across the app.

```tsx
export interface MyComponentProps extends Omit<React.HTMLAttributes<HTMLDivElement>, 'onChange'> {
  value: string;
  onChange: (value: string) => void;
}

export const MyComponent = React.forwardRef<HTMLDivElement, MyComponentProps>(
  ({ value, onChange, className, ...props }, ref) => {
    return <div ref={ref} className={cn('base-styles', className)} {...props} />;
  },
);
MyComponent.displayName = 'MyComponent';
```

## File Organisation (MANDATORY)

Co-locate every non-trivial component in its own directory:

```
components/{domain}/{ComponentName}/
├── index.ts                       ← re-export only
├── {ComponentName}.tsx            ← component implementation (NO constants, NO utility functions)
├── {ComponentName}.types.ts       ← props interface and related types (when needed)
├── {ComponentName}.constants.ts   ← lookup records, label maps, default values (when needed)
├── {ComponentName}.utils.ts       ← pure helper functions scoped to this component (when needed)
└── {ComponentName}.test.tsx       ← tests
```

Simple, single-file components (< 80 lines, no extracted constants or utils needed) may live as a single `.tsx` file without a directory.

## Separation Rule (MANDATORY)

- **Constants** (lookup records, label maps, default objects) must **never** live in `.tsx` files. Extract to `{ComponentName}.constants.ts`.
- **Utility/helper functions** (formatters, transformers, validators) must **never** live in `.tsx` files. Extract to `{ComponentName}.utils.ts`.
- **Types** used only by this component belong in `{ComponentName}.types.ts`.
- The `.tsx` file holds only: the React component, its hooks, and event handlers.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — constants and formatters inside .tsx
const STATUS_LABELS = { pending: 'Pendiente', approved: 'Aprobado' };
function formatAmount(v: number) { return `${v}€`; }
export function MyCard({ status, amount }) { ... }

// ✅ GOOD — clean .tsx, extracted files
// MyCard.constants.ts → STATUS_LABELS
// MyCard.utils.ts     → formatAmount
// MyCard.tsx          → just the component
```

## Styling — Tailwind + cn()

Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for all conditional class merging. Never concatenate class strings manually.

```tsx
import { cn } from '@/lib/utils';

<div className={cn('base px-4 py-2', isActive && 'bg-primary text-white', className)} />
```

Use `cva()` from `class-variance-authority` for variant-driven components:

```tsx
import { cva, type VariantProps } from 'class-variance-authority';

const buttonVariants = cva('inline-flex items-center rounded', {
  variants: {
    variant: {
      default: 'bg-primary text-white',
      outline: 'border border-input',
    },
    size: {
      sm: 'h-8 px-3 text-sm',
      md: 'h-10 px-4',
    },
  },
  defaultVariants: { variant: 'default', size: 'md' },
});

export interface ButtonProps
  extends React.ButtonHTMLAttributes<HTMLButtonElement>,
    VariantProps<typeof buttonVariants> {}
```

Always implement interactive states: `hover:`, `focus-visible:`, `disabled:opacity-50 disabled:cursor-not-allowed`.

## Composition

- Compose multiple small components instead of one large component.
- Extract repeated UI patterns into `components/ui/` (shared) or `components/{domain}/` (domain-specific).
- Pass behaviour via props and callbacks — avoid tight coupling to specific pages or providers.
- Max 300 lines per component file. If exceeded, extract sub-components or move logic to a hook.

## Radix UI

Use Radix primitives for: Select, Dialog, Dropdown, Tooltip, Popover, Tabs, Accordion.
Always include `asChild` support where the Radix primitive supports it.
